{"word":"σύμφημι","slug":"σύμφημι","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>σύμφημι</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>-φήσω</el>) (aor1 <el>συνέφησα</el>) (aor2 <el>συνέφην</el>) </el><p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to assent, approve</i>, or <i>agree fully</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> rei, <i>to concede, agree to, grant</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>; <a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a>, <el>ξύμφημί σοι</el> <i>I grant</i> you, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>; <el>ξύμφαθι ἢ ἄπειπε</el> <i>say yes</i> or no, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> et <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a> <i>to agree</i> that . . , <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>4. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a> <a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <i>to promise</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}